quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,29,"Believers, if you fear God, He will grant you the ability to discriminate between right and wrong, and will forgive you your sins: for God is limitless in His great bounty"
  8,30,"Remember how those who bent on denying the truth plotted against you to imprison you or kill you or expel you: they schemed -- but God also schemed. God is the best of schemers"
  8,31,"Whenever Our revelations are recited to them, they say, \"We have heard them. If we wished, we could produce the like. They are nothing but the fables of the ancients"
  8,32,"They also said, \"God, if this really is the truth from You, then rain down upon us stones from heaven, or send us some other painful punishment"
  8,33,"But God would not punish them while you [Prophet] were in their midst, nor would He punish them so long as they sought forgiveness"
  8,34,"Yet why should God not punish them when they debar people from the Sacred Mosque, although they are not its guardians? Its rightful guardians are those who fear God, though most of them do not realize it"
  8,35,"Their prayers at the Sacred House are nothing but whistling and clapping of hands. \"So taste the punishment because of your denial"
  8,36,"Those who are bent on denying the truth are spending their wealth in debarring others from the path of God. They will continue to spend it in this way till, in the end, this spending will become a source of intense regret for them, and then they will be overcome. And those who denied the truth will be gathered together in Hell"
  8,37,"So that God may separate the bad from the good, He will heap the wicked one upon another and then cast them into Hell. These will surely be the losers"